{{Infobox Journal | discipline = [[Ecology]] | cover = | website = http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/journal.asp?ref=1442-9985 | publisher = [[Blackwell Science Asia]] | country = [[Australia]] | abbreviation = Austral Ecol. | history = 1976–present | frequency = Eight issues per year | ISSN = 1442-9985 | eISSN = 1442-9993 }} '''''Austral Ecology: A Journal of Ecology in the Southern Hemisphere''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[Academic journal|journal]] that publishes original research related to the [[ecology]] of land, marine and freshwater systems in the [[Southern Hemisphere]]. Published by [[Blackwell Science Asia]], it is the official journal of the [[Ecological Society of Australia]].
First published in 1976 as '''''Australian Journal of Ecology''''', it adopted its current name in 2000. There are eight issues per year. As of early 2007 there have been 32 volumes. At that time it had an [[impact factor]] of 1.769. Its [[ISSN]]s are {{ISSN|1442-9985}} for the print edition, and {{ISSN|1442-9993}} for the online edition.<ref name="Journal Home">{{cite web|title=Austral Ecology - Journal Home |url=http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/journal.asp?ref=1442-9985 |publisher=Blackwell Publishing |accessdate=2007-04-13 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070406113407/http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/journal.asp?ref=1442-9985 |archivedate=6 April 2007 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref name="Aims and Scope">{{cite web|title=Austral Ecology - Aims and Scope |url=http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/aims.asp?ref=1442-9985&site=1 |publisher=Blackwell Publishing |accessdate=2007-04-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070804015708/http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/aims.asp?ref=1442-9985&site=1 |archivedate=2007-08-04 |df= }}</ref>
