{{Infobox UK legislation |short_title = Dogs (Protection of Livestock) Act 1953 |type = Act |parliament = |long_title =An Act to provide for the punishment of persons whose dogs worry livestock on agricultural land; and for purposes connected with the matter aforesaid. |year = 1953 |citation = |introduced_by = |territorial_extent = |replaces = |amends = |royal_assent =14 July 1953 |commencement = |repeal_date = |amendments = |repealing_legislation= |related_legislation = |status = |original_text = |legislation_history = |revised_text = |theyworkforyou = |millbankhansard = |use_new_UK-LEG = yes |UK-LEG_title = }}
The '''Dogs (Protection of Livestock) Act of 1953''' is a [[Great Britain|British]] Act devised to protect [[livestock]] from [[dog]]s. The Act outlines punishment of dog owners whose dogs worry livestock on [[agricultural land]]. Protected livestock is defined as [[cattle]], [[sheep]], [[goats]], [[swine]], [[horse]]s and domestic [[poultry]]. [[Game bird]]s are specifically excluded.<ref name='OPSI'>{{cite web|url=http://www.opsi.gov.uk/RevisedStatutes/Acts/ukpga/1953/cukpga_19530028_en_1 |title=Dogs (Protection of Livestock) Act 1953 |accessdate=2009-01-08 |year=1999 |website=Office of Public Sector Information |publisher=Office of Public Sector Information }}</ref><ref name='defra'>{{cite web|url=http://www.defra.gov.uk/animalh/welfare/domestic/dogs.htm |title=Animal welfare: The Control of Dogs |accessdate=2009-01-08 |date=2005-07-12 |publisher=Department for Environment Food and Rural Affairs (defra) |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224040524/http://www.defra.gov.uk/animalh/welfare/domestic/dogs.htm |archivedate=2008-12-24 |df= }}</ref>
