{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
In [[political science]], a '''first-order election''' is among the most important [[election]]s in a nation. In most [[democracies]] these are the national [[parliament]]ary elections, though for some they are the [[presidential election]]s, as in the [[United States]].

