[[File:Gottlob Conrad Christian Storr 1819.jpg|right|thumb|Gottlieb Conrad Christian Storr (1749–1821).]] '''Gottlieb Conrad Christian Storr''' (June 16, 1749 in [[Stuttgart]] – February 27, 1821 in [[Tübingen]]) was a [[Germany|German]] [[physician]], [[chemist]] and [[natural history|naturalist]].
In 1768 he obtained his doctorate from the [[University of Tübingen]], where from 1774 to 1801, he served as a professor of chemistry, [[botany]] and natural history.<ref name=MN>[http://www.minrec.org/libdetail.asp?id=1345 Curtis Schuh’s Biobibliography of Mineralogy. The Mineralogical Record] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130326062043/http://minrec.org/libdetail.asp?id=1345 |date=2013-03-26 }} biographical information</ref> He is the [[taxonomic authority]] of the genus ''[[Mellivora]]'', whose only species is the [[honey badger]] (''Mellivora capensis'').<ref>[https://www.gbif.org/species/107440672 GBIF] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222053425/http://www.gbif.org/species/107440672 |date=2014-02-22 }} Mellivora Storr, 1780</ref><ref>[http://www.bioone.org/doi/abs/10.1644/721?journalCode=mmsp Bioone Mammalian Species] Mellivora capensis</ref>
== Published works == In 1781 he performed extensive scientific investigations in the [[Swiss Alps]], publishing "''Alpenreise vom Jahre 1781''" (1784–86, 2 volumes) as a result.<ref name=MN/> Other noted written efforts by Storr include: * "Dissertatio inauguralis medica, de curis viperinis", 1768 (with [[Ferdinand Christoph Oetinger]] 1719–1772). * ''Entwurf einer Folge von Unterhaltungen zur Einleitung in die Naturgeschichte'', 1777. * ''Ueber seine Bearbeitungsart der Naturgeschichte'', 1780. * "Investigandae crystallifodinarum oeconomiae quaedam pericula", 1785.<ref>[http://orlabs.oclc.org/identities/lccn-no94-28115/ WorldCat Identities] Most widely held works by Gottlieb Konrad Christian Storr</ref><ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/identities/np-storr,%20gottlieb%20konrad%20christian$chemiker%20botaniker%20mediziner$1749%201821/ WorldCat] Storr, Gottlieb Konrad Christian Chemiker, Botaniker, Mediziner 1749-1821</ref> * [https://books.google.com/books?id=hKpAAAAAcAAJ "Idea methodi fossilium"], 1807.
