'''Grus Wall''' is a superstructure of [[galaxies]] ("[[wall of galaxies]]").<ref>{{cite book |last1=Maurogordato |first1=S. |title=Clustering in the Universe: Proceedings of the XXXth Rencontres de Moriond, Les Arcs, Savoie, France, March 11-18, 1995 |date=1995 |publisher=Atlantica Séguier Frontières |isbn=9782863321898 |page=69 |accessdate=11 October 2018|url=https://books.google.ru/books?id=g0-suNqbrUwC&pg=PA69&dq=Grus+Wall&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiFxo7J_P3dAhULjiwKHbWZCy8Q6AEINTAD#v=onepage&q=Grus%20Wall&f=false}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=S |first1=Maddox |last2=Aragon-salamanca |first2=Alfonso |title=Wide Field Spectroscopy And The Distant Universe - Proceedings Of The 35th Herstmonceux Conference |date=May 31, 1995 |publisher=World Scientific |isbn=9789814550147 |page=124 |url=https://books.google.ru/books?id=g0-suNqbrUwC&pg=PA69&dq=Grus+Wall&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiFxo7J_P3dAhULjiwKHbWZCy8Q6AEINTAD#v=onepage&q=Grus%20Wall&f=false |accessdate=11 October 2018}}</ref> The Grus Wall is "perpendicular" to the [[Fornax Wall]] and [[Sculptor Wall]].<ref name=LSSg>''Astrophysics and Space Science'', Volume 230, Issue 1-2, pp. 225-235 "Large-Scale Structures in the Distribution of Galaxies" ''08/1995'' {{bibcode|1995Ap&SS.230..225F}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=O'Meara |first1=Stephen James |title=Deep-Sky Companions: Southern Gems |date=April 8, 2013 |publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]] |isbn=9781107015012 |page=107 |url=https://books.google.ru/books?id=S5QIEKns33sC&pg=PA107&lpg=PA107&dq=Grus+Wall+astronomy&source=bl&ots=Qlw009yZaw&sig=8HSEHH3CkKFxqs2hPk9erbzbUng&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjgucj9-_3dAhUDCCwKHYKfD0EQ6AEwDXoECAAQAQ#v=onepage&q=Grus%20Wall%20astronomy&f=false |accessdate=11 October 2018}}</ref> 

